title: Date of the contract
explanation: The contract states: 'SCHEDULE to the 2002 ISDA MASTER AGREEMENT dated as of December 30, 2015', which clearly provides the date.

title: Party A
explanation: The text specifies: 'CAPITAL ONE, NATIONAL ASSOCIATION ( "Party A")', which clearly identifies Party A.

title: party_B
explanation: The text specifies: 'MACK-CALI REALTY, L.P. ( "Party B")', which clearly identifies Party B.

title: Specified entity Party A
explanation: The text explicitly states: 'Specified Entity means in relation to Party A, None.'

title: Specified entity Party B
explanation: The text explicitly states: 'Specified Entity means in relation to Party B, None.'

title: Specified transaction scope
explanation: The text states that 'Specified Transaction' will have the meaning specified in Section 14, indicating the standard definition is used without modification.

title: Cross default applicable parties
explanation: The text states that the Cross Default provisions will apply to Party A and will apply to Party B, indicating both parties are subject to Cross Default.

title: Specified indebtness includes borrowed_money
explanation: The text does not mention 'borrowed money' specifically, nor does it explicitly include or exclude it from Specified Indebtedness.

title: Specified indebtness excludes deposits
explanation: The text explicitly states that Specified Indebtedness shall not include obligations in respect of deposits received in the ordinary course of a party's banking business.

title: amount for Party A
explanation: The threshold for Party A is defined as a percentage, not a fixed amount.

title: currency for Party A
explanation: No currency is specified for Party A, as the threshold is a percentage of shareholders' equity.

title: percentage for Party A
explanation: The text states 'an amount equal to 3% of the shareholders' equity of Party A'.

title: percentage reference for Party A
explanation: The reference is 'shareholders' equity of Party A', which matches the SHAREHOLDER enum.

title: amount for Party B
explanation: The text states 'in relation to Party B, $50,000,000.'

title: currency for Party B
explanation: The $ symbol indicates US dollars.

title: percentage for Party B
explanation: No percentage threshold is specified for Party B, only a fixed amount.

title: percentage reference for Party B
explanation: No percentage threshold is specified for Party B.

title: Credit Event Upon Merger  applicable parties
explanation: The text states the 'Credit Event Upon Merger' provisions will apply to Party A and will apply to Party B.

title: Automatic Early Termination  applicable parties
explanation: The text explicitly states that Automatic Early Termination will not apply to Party A and will not apply to Party B, so it applies to no party.

title: Termination Currency
explanation: The text explicitly states that 'Termination Currency' means United States Dollars, which corresponds to the ISO code USD.

title: Email for notices for Party A
explanation: The email for notices to Party A is explicitly listed as 'Email: tradingops@capitalone.com' under the address for Party A.

title: Email for notices for Party B
explanation: The email for notices to Party B is explicitly listed as 'Email: bfitzpatrick@mack-cali.com' under the address for Party B. The Chatham Financial email is for a copy, not the main notice.

title: Process agent for party A
explanation: The text states 'Party A appoints as its Process Agent: Not applicable.' indicating no process agent for Party A.

explanation: Not applicable is specified for Party A, so no name is provided.

title: Party B is a Multibranch party

title: Party for calculation agent
explanation: The text explicitly states 'The Calculation Agent is Party A', with a provision for substitution only if an Event of Default occurs with respect to Party A.
